fields.description:
While investigating support case we found a few problems with logic of matching linkers to commit messages.

We defined following global linkers:
{noformat}
[a-zA-Z0-9]{2,}-\d+ [A-Za-z] href: http://syseng.pelco.org/tests/${0}
[a-zA-Z0-9]{2,}- href: http://dp.pl/${0}
{noformat} 

Repository specific links:
{noformat}
[a-zA-Z0-9]{2,}-\d+ href: http://syseng.pelco.org/XXX/tasks/browse/${0}
.+ href: http://jjdp.pl/${0}
{noformat}

We scanned repository (will be attached) and in the result we got following matches:

{noformat}
"asd ABC-666 asdad" resulted in: <a href="http://jjdp.pl/asd ABC-666 asdad">asd ABC-666 asdad</a>
"ABC-666 asdad" resulted in: <a href="http://syseng.pelco.org/XXX/tasks/browse/ABC-666">ABC-666</a><a href="http://jjdp.pl/ asdad"> asdad</a>
"asdad ABC-123" resulted in: <a href="http://jjdp.pl/asdad ABC-123">asdad ABC-123</a>
"ABC-666 asdad" resulted in: <a href="http://syseng.pelco.org/XXX/tasks/browse/ABC-666">ABC-666</a><a href="http://jjdp.pl/ asdad"> asdad</a>
{noformat}

I'd expect that .+ would match everything.

What we also found is that when global linker regex matches more characters than project specific it will be used (instead of project specific). That's not intuitive - I'd expect that when I have project specific settings the global ones will not be used?

Attaching subversion repository used for testing and config.xml

Also if you modify linkers they are not refreshed automatically: in case of CVS you only have to restart repository, in case of Subversion you need to re-index it. There's no information in UI (after or during you change linkers) describing how to trigger re-indexing of them.

I added subversion repository to FishEye. URL pointed to local repository (using file scheme - file:///). I didn't specify any other options. Test connection returned true. Unfortunately while trying to browse repository I got:

{noformat}
Unable to initialise repository file://... due to com.cenqua.fisheye.config.ConfigException:Unable to get repository information: org.tigris.subversion.javahl.ClientException: svn: Unable to open an ra_local session to URL svn: Unable to open repository 'file:///....' svn: Local URL 'file://...' contains unsupported hostname
{noformat}

I attached also screenshots.

This means that you can't restart Fisheye after adding a trusted application. The workaround is to manually edit your config.xml file after stopping fisheye, adding
{code}
<certificateTimeout>1000</certificateTimeout>
{code}
inside each {{<trustedApplication>}} element.
